<BaseLayout title="Germany immigration crime statistics: BKA official data | Immigration Factbook" lang="en" altHref="/faq/germany-immigration-crime/" description="Germany's Federal Criminal Police (BKA) 2023: non-German nationals show a 5.36% suspect rate vs 1.46% for German nationals — a 3.7× ratio. Age, urban concentration, and socioeconomic factors explain most of the gap.">
<main class="theme-page">
  <div class="theme-hero">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">Immigration Factbook</a> › <span>FAQ</span></nav>
    <div class="theme-hero__badge">BKA (Federal Criminal Police Office) — Polizeiliche Kriminalstatistik 2023</div>
    <h1>Germany: Immigration &amp; Crime<br>BKA Official Data<em>3.7× suspect rate ratio</em></h1>
    <p class="theme-hero__sub">BKA 2023: non-German nationals 5.36% suspect rate vs 1.46% for German nationals (~3.7×). Age structure, urban concentration, and socioeconomic factors explain most of the gap.</p>
    <div class="theme-hero__meta">
      <span class="lang-pill"><a href="/faq/germany-immigration-crime/">🌐 日本語</a></span>
      <span class="meta-note">Primary official sources only</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Key figures (BKA PKS 2023)</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Indicator</th><th>Figure</th><th>Source</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Non-German nationals — suspect rate (per capita)</td>
          <td><strong>5.36%</strong></td>
          <td><a href="https://www.bka.de" rel="noopener">BKA PKS 2023</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>German nationals — suspect rate (per capita)</td>
          <td><strong>1.46%</strong></td>
          <td>BKA PKS 2023</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Ratio (non-German / German)</td>
          <td>~3.7×</td>
          <td>BKA PKS 2023 (calculated)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Data type</td>
          <td>Police crime statistics (PKS) — suspects, not convictions</td>
          <td>BKA</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Factors explaining the gap</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Age composition:</strong> Non-German nationals have a higher share of young men — the demographic group with the highest crime rates across all populations. This alone accounts for a substantial portion of the raw ratio.</li>
      <li><strong>Urban concentration:</strong> Most non-German nationals live in large cities, which have higher crime rates overall regardless of population origin.</li>
      <li><strong>Socioeconomic status:</strong> Average income and employment rates are lower among non-German nationals. Poverty correlates with crime rates across all nationalities.</li>
      <li><strong>Suspects vs. convictions:</strong> PKS counts suspects, not convictions. Policing intensity and reporting patterns can affect who is counted.</li>
      <li><strong>Nationality vs. immigrant background:</strong> Second-generation immigrants born in Germany often hold German nationality and are counted in the "German national" category. BKA does not classify by immigrant background — only by nationality.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Cross-country comparison</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Country</th><th>Ratio (immigrant / native-born)</th><th>Source &amp; measure</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Germany</td><td>3.7× suspect rate</td><td>BKA PKS 2023 (by nationality)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sweden</td><td>~2.5× suspect rate</td><td>BRÅ 2021 (by immigrant background)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Denmark</td><td>2.6× suspect rate (age-adjusted)</td><td>DST (immigrants &amp; descendants vs. Danish-origin)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>United States</td><td>No systematic federal cross-tabulation</td><td>FBI UCR / BJS (no immigration status variable)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="table-note">Direct comparison requires caution: Germany classifies by nationality; Sweden and Denmark classify by immigrant background. These are different population categories.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Primary source</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Bundeskriminalamt (2023). <em>Polizeiliche Kriminalstatistik (PKS) 2023</em>. <a href="https://www.bka.de" rel="noopener">www.bka.de</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

